<recipe>
    <name>Coq Au Vin</name>
    <indexCharacter>C</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Combine salt, pepper and flour; rub into chicken. Brown chicken in butter in a Dutch oven or casserole. Add small white onions, shallots, chopped onions, garlic and mushroom caps; cook over low heat until onions brown lightly. Add wine, thyme and bay leaf; cook over low heat 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. The last stage can also be slow cooked in a crockpot.</instructions>
